         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">22/9/82 ¶  ¶ The alpine plant, just received from you, dear Mr Buchanan, ¶  is Carpha alpina (R. Br.) in an luxurious state. ¶  ¶ Could you let me have specimens of your new Mitrasacmes? ¶  The extra-...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">82.09.22a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Buchanan</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A644, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">22/9/82</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The alpine plant, just received from you, dear Mr Buchanan,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>John Buchanan (1819-1898).</p>
               </note> is <name key="Carpha%20alpina">Carpha alpina</name> (R. Br.) in an luxurious state.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Could you let me have specimens of your new <name key="Mitrasacme">Mitrasacme</name>s?<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Buchanan (1882a), pp. 348-9 and plate 22.</p>
               </note> The extra-australian few species interest me much.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I enclose my card for Mr Travers with a few words thereon.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Card not found.</p>
               </note> Perhaps you will kindly transmit it to him.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Is there any chance of the N.Z. Government bringing out a special edition of my "select plants for industrial culture" as was done 1881 in the Gov Printing Office of Sydney<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B81.13.10.</p>
               </note> &amp; in 1880 in Calcutta<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B80.13.07.</p>
               </note> &amp; this year (in Germany) at Cassel.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The German edition B83.13.06 is dated 1883 on the title page, although the notice of it in <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Botanische Jahrbcher für Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie</seg>, vol. 4 (1883), p. 499 reports it as published in 1882. No New Zealand edition was published.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Carpha%20alpina">Carpha alpina</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Mitrasacme">Mitrasacme</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
